credit_line: Bequest of Mrs. Henry E. Coe
title: Sampler
provenance: ex. coll. Mrs. Henry E. Coe (Eva Johnston Coe)
medium:
Medium: silk embroidery on wool foundation
Technique: embroidered in cross, eyelet, stem, and satin stitches on plain weave foundation
description:
In the center are several bands of neatly worked alphabets, a verse, crowns, the initials HH and the inscription Hannah Holland My Work in the Year 1755.
At the top and bottom are very crudely embroidered elements: birds, flowering trees, and a leopard. It seems probable that the top and bottom were not worked by Hannah Holland, the embroiderer of the alphabets.
name: Sampler
